Job Description

To handle mortgage referral applications and enquiries;
Identify sales opportunities and develop new business in mortgage
To solicit and generate revenue growth on mortgage loan business through various sales activities;
To establish and develop a good business relationship with referral parties including mortgage intermediaries, property agencies, mortgage brokers, banks and other sales channels;
To achieve individual targets on mortgage lending;
To evaluate potential credit risk to ensure loan proceedings in compliance with procedural and documentation requirements;


Requirements

At least 5 years’ experience gained from local money lender companies in mortgage loan development business;
Good track record in mortgage sales, with extensive network with mortgage intermediaries/agents/banks/property agencies;
With a strong potential client network is an advantage;
Good communication, presentation and interpersonal skills;
Proactive, motivated, good market sense and sales-oriented;
Good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Immediate available is highly preferred

We offer competitive remuneration package, our benefits include:

Performance bonus
Education subsidy
Professional membership fee sponsorship
Life & medical insurance
Marriage Leave, Compassionate Leave, Examination Leave etc.
Public holidays
Staff purchase discount

Interested parties please send full resume with present and expected salary to Human Resources Department by clicking Apply Now.

(Information provided will be treated in strict confidence and will only be used for recruitment-related purposes.)

Our client is a reputable Bank, now they are seeking a professional to join their Remittance Department.



Responsibilities

Handle remittance transactions in professional manner;
Conduct customer contact and handle customer enquires;
Prepare daily and management reports;
Handle system enhancement projects from time to time;
Complete work tasks as assigned by management and team leader.

Requirements:

Post-secondary education;
Minimum 6 years of relevant experience;
Familiar with regulatory requirements of cross border Renminbi settlement as well as SWIFT/Telex handling;
Hands-on experience in trade or settlement transaction is an advantage;
Good interpersonal and communication skills with good time management;
Good command of spoken English, Cantonese, and Putonghua;
Candidates with more experiencse can be considered as Manager.

Interested parties please forward your CV in word format with current and expected salaries to PICCO Bent Consultancy Limited.

[All applications will be treated with strict confidential and will be used for recruitment purposes only]

Responsibilities:


•           Prepare facility letters, loan documents and relevant correspondences such as instruction letter to solicitor firms;

•           Perform the checker role for reviewing the basic facility letters and/or loan documentations prepared by the marker if necessary;

•           Perform loan documentation review prior to the loan drawdown/ line validation;

•           Process the regular MIS reports;

•           Participate in UAT project;

•           Participate in monthly outstanding cases clean-up exercise and/or yearly files cleaning up project;

•           Assist supervisor in drafting and reviewing the operation manual;

•           Ordering and reviewing of valuation report;

•           Perform ad hoc duties as assigned;

•           Reply follow-up issues as requested by LPS;

•           Deliver loan documents and/or other relevant documents to various business units and/or other relevant parties

Requirements:



Degree holder, preferably in Business or related disciplines
Minimum 4 years of loan documentation and credit execution experience
Strong command of spoken and written English and Chinese (including Putonghua)

Wholesale Banking COO Office

Hang Seng's Wholesale Banking business provides a broad spectrum of financing solutions to large corporations and financial institutions. As a strategic financial partner to corporate customers, Hang Seng offers a comprehensive range of products and services including bilateral and syndication loans, project financing, property development financing, property investment loans, working capital financing, trade financing, cash management and treasury products. Our experienced and knowledgeable professionals understand the specific requirements of our customers and are committed to providing tailor-made financial packages in their best interests.

We are currently seeking a high caliber professional to join our department as Proposition Manager.


Principal responsibilities

Perform analysis and provide key insights on portfolio management in managing Wholesale lending assets to optimize balance sheet capacity with focusing on capital efficiency and reward;
Assist in the execution of lending related initiatives which support business strategies and achieve financial goal;
Oversee the regulatory compliance related to credit and lending and responsible for related regulatory returns;
Drive and coordinate the IT enhancement, digital lending and data management projects;
Ensure the timely and quality deliverables to meet the expectation of our key stakeholders

Requirements

University degree in a related discipline or other relevant qualifications; 
Minimum of 5 years' experience in banking industry, preferably with experience in lending proposition, business development / business management; 
Sound knowledge in portfolio management, Bank’s governance framework and regulatory requirements on corporate customers; 
Strong attentiveness to detail, resilient and ability to work responsibly in a dynamic environment; 
Creative, curious and with sound analytical and problem solving skills; 
Ability to manage multiple stakeholders and manage conflicts, high connectivity, capable to drive change and transformation effectively; 
Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese; 
Great sense of ownership and servicing mindset to ensure efficient and effective customer service processes
If you would like to explore other opportunities at Hang Seng Hong Kong, please visit www.hangseng.com/careers/ for details.
The health and safety of our employees and candidates is very important to us. Due to the current situation related to the Novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV), we’re leveraging our digital capabilities to ensure we can continue to recruit top talent at the HSBC Group. As your application progresses, you may be asked to use one of our digital tools to help you through your recruitment journey. If so, one of our Resourcing colleagues will explain how our video-interviewing technology will be used throughout the recruitment process and will be on hand to answer any questions you might have.
All information provided by applicants will be used only for recruitment purposes and will be used strictly in accordance with the Bank's personal data policies, a copy of which may be obtained by the applicant upon request. Unless otherwise instructed in writing by the applicant concerned, applicants may be considered for other suitable positions within the Bank and its related companies. The personal data of unsuccessful job applicants may be retained for a maximum of two years from the date when the job application is rejected and such data may be retained for a longer period if there is a subsisting reason that obliges the Bank to do so, after which the personal data will be destroyed.

Duties & Responsibilities

Perform Syndication Agency function and loan administration as an officer;
Processing of bilateral loans and syndicated loans;
Process customer due diligent (KYC);
Review the draft of structured & syndicated loan documentation, and to ensure all terms and conditions as well as security arrangements are properly structured according to the bank’s policy.
To work closely with other departments for loan draw down and other operation activities;
Liaise with legal counsels and marketing units to ensure proper and efficient operations of credit administration work;
Monitor & follow up documentation deficiency and outstanding loan documents;
Maintain the documentation tracking and filing system;
Ensure the collateral, securities documents, conditions precedent, financial covenants and insurance documents are complied with loan agreements;
Correspondence to all enquiries, requirements and ad hot events from loans related parties;
Handle Trade Finance operation jobs if required.

 Education & Experience:

Post-secondary or above
3 years’ experience in syndicated loan operation, or related job preferably
Knowledge of loan documentation, procedures and relevant requirement
Willing to work both syndicated loan and Trade Finance operations
Good command of written and spoken English.
Good command of written and spoken Korean is preferable.
Good knowledge of MS Office



Attractive remuneration packages along with annual discretionary bonus and generous employee benefits to the right candidates

